Dexia to Set Up 90 Billion-Euro Bad Bank, De Standaard Reports

-- B y   A o i f e   W h i t e
-- 
2011-10-09T19:19:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-09/dexia-to-set-up-90-billion-euro-bad-bank-de-standaard-reports.html
Dexia SA (DEXB)  will set up a “bad bank”
with 90 billion euros of troubled assets with  Belgium  providing
a guarantee for 60 percent of the amount, De Standaard reported,
without saying where it obtained the information.  Belgium would provide a guarantee of 54 billion euros,
while  France  would guarantee 33 billion euros and Luxembourg
almost 3 billion euros, according to the newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aoife White in Brussels at 
 awhite62@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
